HEADWORD: Homonymous
<hw>Ho*mon"y*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>homonymus</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/ the same + <?/, for <?/ name; akin to
E. <ets>name</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the same name or
designation; standing in the same relation; -- opposed to
<xex>heteronymous</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having the same name or designation, but different
meaning or relation; hence, equivocal; ambiguous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homonymously</ent>⟦br⟧
